column2: Calm- mostly sunny- no boating traffic- loons out earlier- water very clear- and little weed growth.
Calm- mostly sunny- small algae particles in water- water super clear- and weed growth not high.  Took readings three times to verify.
Calm- cloudy- lots of rain lately- and boat traffic has been moderate except for jet sking (high).
Northeast wind- windy- sunny- water appears clearer- and baby loons came within 30 feet of us.
Mostly sunny- some wind- and water is very clear.  Loons and babies are gone.
Light south wind and sunny.  Few deep weeds.  Numerous floating weed bogs in NW bay.
Mostly cloudy and windy.  It was hot for seven days and the last 3-4 days have been cool (70s) and windy.
Mostly cloudy- no wind- and cool weather.
partly cloudy-light wind- extremely clear water despite rain the last three days
somewhat hazy-warm+ humid- light s.w. wind-water still very clear and much warmer than May
mostly sunny- rained 1/2 inch last night- s.w. wind 10 mph- water still clear but not as much as June
cloudy but warm- alot of rain during the last 10 days- yearling loons still on the lake
Cloudy but warm- lots of rain during the last 7-10 days- and the 2 baby loons are still on the lake.
partly sunny- windy water very clear.
partly sunny-light wind-rained last night but the

column1: water is still very clear- 4 loons on the lake this year normally only two

column2: clear and light wind/temp 70-little humidity peaceful
Cloudy- rain last 2 days.  Water not as clear as in past years at this time.
Cloudy- some sun.  Water clarity poor.  Weather has been cool and rainy.
Sunny- calm- warm.  Lake very clear.  Better than May + June.  Weather has been cool.
cloudy- very windy- cool dissolved oxygen very good at 35ft!
cloudy- 53F- light wind- water not as clear- lots of rain lately- leaves in water
sunny- light wind- water very clean and clear
sunny- warm- humid- light wind- rained last night
mostly sunny- wind 10 mph- lots of rain and snow last week
partly sunny-light southeast wind- water very clear
partly sunny- light wind- temp 70- water very clear
sunny 65-light sw wind water very clear
clear-nice sunny day but windy.Lots of rain the last 5-7 days
Sunny and humid- lots of rain lately
Sunny and cool:. Cool spring so far this year
Lake level several inches high due to 6+ inches of rain recently. Today sunny warm with a light sw wind
Sunny-light sw wind- lake level normal.nice day
Sunny- wind moderate from the southwest- temp about 55= pretty spring day
partly sunny 65 degrees light wind very nice morning- 5 inches of rain last week
very nice morning- sunny white clouds and light northeast wind.
Data collected by the White Lake School students during a pontoon classroom. The students were fantastic.

column1: The weather has been quiet for days. The day is sunny and the lake calm.

column2: Grades 3 and 4 and 5 and 6 from White Lake School learned how to collect Secchi data. Also took a temperature and DO profile. Secchi disk readings ranged from 11.75 to 17.00 feet. We took an average for SWIMS.
partly sunny 72 degrees moderate winds. Water top 15 feet cooler than normal do to cool days and nights.
Partly cloudy nice breeze. Ice out late 5/7 but hot the last few days.  Thus water very warm at the top for this time of year but cold below 10 feet
Cloudy moderate northwest wind.Choppy water with no sun  probably effected secchi depth reading
